Locals Privacy Policy
Last updated: December 31, 2024
This privacy policy explains how we,
Locals Ltd
of Gladstonos 12-14, 8046 Paphos, Cyprus or any of our affiliated entities (
“Locals”, “we”, “us”, “our”
), process your personal information (
“you”, “your”
) when you use our website, app or other services.
PLEASE READ THIS PRIVACY POLICY CAREFULLY.
By using the Locals mobile application (the
“App”
) or the website located at https://locals.org/ (the
“Website”
) (App and Website individually referred to individually as a
“Locals Service”
or collectively as the
“Locals Services”
) or otherwise indicating your acceptance (e.g. by clicking tick-box or bottom “agree” or continue”), you agree to the following terms of our Privacy Policy, which will bind you at all times and in whatever manner you use the Locals Services.
Please note:
Individuals in the
European Economic Area (EEA)
and the
United Kingdom (UK)
should read our section about
“Your EEA & UK Data Privacy Rights”
.
Individuals from
United States
should also read our section on
“Your United States Privacy Rights”
.
Where this Privacy Policy apply to
This Privacy Policy applies to all Locals Services.
This Privacy Policy does not apply to information that you have directly provided to other users, including Creators, Club group admins, and others with whom you may share information about yourself out of Locals Services.
What types of information do we collect
Generally,
“personal information”
,
“personal data”
or similar terms refer to any information that identifies you or relates to you. However, the exact meaning of personal information may be determined by the law of the country of your residence.
We will process the following information which may be considered personal information:
Information you provide to us directly
Profile Data:
Your
user details
when you sign up as a user of Locals Services; Information, such as your username, name, surname, date of birth, age, gender, your city or place, your profile image.
Information that you provide about your
goal, professional area, interests and occupation
or that Locals otherwise collect about your
preferences and interests
known, observed or inferred.
Your social media usernames and (or) links to your profiles.
For safety reasons this information will be available to Verified Members only, unless you
opt-out
at any time. You will be free to edit or remove such information at any time if you no longer wish to share such information. Your Instagram ID and your Instagram photo-stream, if you choose to link your Locals account to your Instagram account.
Sensitive personal information
, if you choose to provide it, for example in your bio. This could be information such as, for example, about your political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, health or sexual orientation. It’s your choice whether to include sensitive information on your profile and to make that sensitive information public. Please be aware that your activity while using Locals Services sometimes may make available some of your sensitive information. For instance, the mere fact of voluntary joining certain Activities (e.g. Clubs) to some extent may indicate information about your health, religion, political views, or sexual identity. Please do not post or add personal data to your profile that you would not want to be publicly available. If you choose to use our Locals Services and to share sensitive personal information on it (e.g., as part of your biography, in a message, by joining a topic-based Club or via event invite), this will constitute your explicit consent to our processing that information. You will be free to edit or remove such information at any time if you no longer wish to share such information.
Content generated by you
. To the extent permitted, necessary and sufficient by applicable laws and Locals Privacy Policy, we may review, scan, or analyze your communications within Locals Services and the content you post with us for reasons outlined in the “How We Use Information” below, including fraud prevention, security investigations, risk assessment, regulatory compliance, product development, research, analytics, enforcing our Terms of Service, and content moderation purposes. For example, as part of our Locals improvement efforts and to expand product offerings, we may scan and analyse messages and materials uploaded to the App in message threads, profiles, Activities. In some cases, we may also review or analyse your chats with other Users and content published by you for the purpose of identifying and reporting content violations or inappropriate activities to appropriate authorities. We use automated methods where reasonably possible. Occasionally we may need to manually review communications, such as for fraud investigations and content moderations, or to assess and improve the functionality of these automated tools. We will not review, scan, or analyze your messaging communications to send third-party marketing messages to you and we will not sell reviews or analyses of these communications.
You can choose what information to share on your profile. You don’t have to provide additional information on your profile; however, profile information helps you to get more from our Locals Services. Be cautious when sharing information, as it may become visible to other users.
Contact details
such as your telephone number and email address.
Details of your request.
When you contact or visit us, we may process the details of your request, communications, complaints, or other interaction.
Activity data.
Information you provide to us when you participate in any interactive features of Locals Services, including surveys, contests, promotions; when you join and interact with Activities, for example Clubs and Private Activity. Your choice of Activities is entirely voluntary and also optional, but we are required to process this information in order to administer your account, and to indicate that you are a Participant of the Activities that you join.
Information we collect automatically
Transaction information
such as information about your purchases and donations in Locals Services, including date of donation / purchase, currency, amount, payment type and the last four digits of your card number. This data is used to provide you with Locals Services and for our in-app analytics.
Device information.
When accessing our Locals Services, your
device
and
browser
will automatically provide unique information such as account ID, mobile device ID, internet protocol (IP) address, cookie ID or online identifiers, app settings and characteristics, and identifiers associated with cookies or other technologies that may uniquely identify a device or browser operating system, browser type, time zone setting, location and date and time of access.
(If you have provided your consent)
IDFA or Android Advertising ID, whichever is applicable to your device. You may disable the collection of IDFA and/or Android Advertising ID by Locals, in the setting of your mobile device. We and third-parties may use cookies, Software Development Kits (SDKs), and other tracking technologies to automatically collect the Personal Data set forth above. For more information regarding our use of these technologies, please see our
Cookie Notice
.
Usage data.
Our systems may record usage data about how you navigate, engage and interact with our Locals Services, for instance how you use them (e.g. when you logged in, features you’ve been using, actions taken, information shown to you, referring webpages address) and your interactions with other users (e.g. users you connect and interact with, and when you communicate  with them).
Information we obtain from third parties
In addition to the information you may provide us directly, we receive information about you from others, including:
Users.
Users may provide information about you as they use our Locals Services, for instance as they interact with you or if they submit a report involving you.
Social media.
You may decide to share information with us through your social media account, such as your interaction with our posts and content, social media profile by sharing your “stories” and ‘likes’ on social media platforms, such as Twitter and Instagram, TikTok.
Our suppliers.
We may receive information about you from our partners where our ads are published on a partner’s service (in which case they may pass along details on a campaign’s success). We may receive information about you from our analytics service providers to help us measure traffic and usage trends with data they collect through Locals Services in accordance with their own privacy policies. A list of the analytic partners that operate in Locals Services can be found in the Appendix A below. Where legally allowed, we can also receive information about suspected or convicted bad actors from third parties, as part of our efforts to ensure our users safety and security.
Other information upon your explicit consent
Location data.
Some of our features rely on
real-time information about the precise location
of your device where you enabled the functionality on your device. If you decline permission for us to collect your precise location, we will not collect it, and those of our Locals Services which rely on location may not be available to you.
Phone contact list.
You may provide access to your phone contact list so that you can choose to invite your phone contacts to join the Locals Services or see which phone contacts are already on the Locals Service and get notified in the future when your contacts download the app. Your Phone Contact List will be periodically synced and stored securely on our servers. If you are the phone contact of a Locals Service user we may use your phone number to invite you to use the Locals Service but only if the existing registered Locals Service user requests that we do this.
Photo verification data.
You may choose to verify your account, using our facial recognition feature, that compares the face in your selfie to the photos in your profile. We collect your verification data upon your consent, which may be considered biometric data in some jurisdictions. We only use your verification information for the purpose of Photo Verification. We do not add the verification photos to your profile. If you choose to verify your profile photo, we will scan each photo that you submit. The scan may include the use of facial recognition technology so that we can compare the photo you submit to your profile photo, to help ensure that you are who you say you are.
Data accuracy
We will rely on the information provided by you as accurate, complete, and up to date, and we would be grateful if you could inform us of any changes.
How we use your information
Generally, we will use your personal information to (i) provide our Locals Services and enable you to use our Locals Services features, (ii) respond to your queries, (iii) develop and promote our organization and services; (iv) ensure the security and technical availability of Locals Services; and (v) comply with the law.
* If you are an individual in the EEA or the UK, we have to inform you about the “legal ground” for us to use your “personal data”. This will typically be the performance of our contract with you (based on our
Terms of Use
) or our legitimate interest to use your personal data to ensure that our services are provided properly, efficiently and securely, as is further explained in the table below.
Where we rely on legitimate interests as the legal basis for processing personal data, we have considered whether or not those interests are overridden by the interests or fundamental rights or freedoms of the individuals whose data are being processed and concluded that the processing is, on balance, fair.
Where the legal basis is consent, you can withdraw consent at any time. You may withdraw your consent by adapting your settings or by deleting your content (for instance where you entered information in your profile that may be considered 'special' or 'sensitive'). In any case, you may withdraw your consent at any time by contacting us at the address provided at the end of this Privacy Policy.
Where the legal basis is legitimate interests, you have a right to object to our use of your data.
