Automated decision-making and profiling
We may use automated decision-making and profiling features for the following reasons:
To help connect you with other users; (including where we use generative AI tools to recommend personalized ideas for activities, as described below).
To show you ads and offers that may be of interest to you.
To promote safety and security. We use a combination of automated systems and a team of moderators to monitor and review accounts (including photos and any other profile data) and messages for content that indicates breaches of our
Terms of Use.
This processing may lead to suspension or account closure for users who are reported to be found to engage in illegal or unauthorized activities, both on and off our services, without prejudice to other legal actions we could take.
We do not intend that these automated decision-making or profiling activities will produce legal or other significant effects for you; please contact us if you think for any reason that this is the case.
No processing of payment details
We will not receive or store any of your payment details – this is fully handled by the relevant payment service provider. If/when you make any purchases in a Locals store, we are notified by the payment processor once the transaction takes place and then ensure you receive your purchase. We do not, however, receive any of your actual payment details or personal data related to the payment. We only keep the data concerning transaction dates, currencies, value, the last four digits of your card number and the subject of the transaction.
Cookies and similar technologies
Please, read our
Cookie Notice
on how we use cookies and similar technologies.
How your information may be shared
We will generally not share your information except with (i) our
third party service providers and advisors
who may process personal information on our behalf, (ii) our
advertising, marketing and analytics partners
, as explained above, (iii) our
group companies
for the purposes set out above, (iv) persons or authorities where we are
compelled by law
, (v) to the relevant entity in case of a merger, acquisition or collaboration, and (vi) other third parties where you have provided your
consent
.
Public profile visibility
When joining Locals Services, you create profile which is displayed publicly by default. This means your public profile is partially visible to people who aren't users, viewers who aren't signed in to Locals Services (in order to see your full profile on Locals Services, visitors may need to log in to their Locals accounts).The following data may be publicly visible:
profile name;
profile image;
your Locals profile creation date;
your bio (optional);
connected social media accounts (optional).
You have full control over what information is displayed. You can modify your profile settings at any time to manage your privacy preferences and access off-Locals visibility (i.e. make your Profile Data unavailable for public viewing off the Locals Service) preferences by contacting us at
privacy@locals.org
.
Sharing with third-parties
From time to time Locals may offer the functionality for you to choose to synchronise your Locals events with third party event platforms and relevant personal information may be shared with such third party event platforms in this case.
We use suppliers to help us operate, distribute, market and improve our Locals Services, such as data hosting and maintenance, analytics, customer care, marketing, advertising, payment processing and security operations. For these purposes, we may share your personal information with our analytics service providers, who utilise generative AI and machine learning tools (e.g., ChatGPT) to perform in-depth analysis and gain valuable insights on Locals Services improvement. We also share information with suppliers who distribute and assist us in advertising our Locals Services. For instance, we may share limited information on you in hashed, non-human readable form to advertising vendors.
We carry out due diligence on all Service Providers we engage to ensure they have adequate data protection and information security measures in place and only provide them with the personal data necessary to the service they are providing. Measures are taken to ensure that the data shared is non-attributable to the greatest extent possible and our suppliers are also subject to extensive obligations under our contractual arrangements, including strict data retention limits.
Sharing with other Users
You share information with other Users when you voluntarily disclose information on Locals Service (including your public Profile data). Your profile data is fully visible to all users and/or visitors of our Locals Services, it can also be visible to others on or off of our Locals Services (e.g., visitors to our Services or users of third-party search engines). You may choose to share other user profiles and they may share yours with people outside of our Locals Services, using the sharing functionality.
Some information about your activity within Local Services, such as registration for or donation to an Activity, including Paid Activity, your Club memberships, participation in or expressing interest in Activity, may be visible to other Users. We recommend that you check the Activity and what information may become available before joining the Activity to ensure that you are happy with the information that may be visible to others.
Sharing with Creators and Club admins
Please also note that some users, such as Creators of Activities or Club group admins, you interact with, may have access to your Personal Data (e.g. Profile data, Contact details) and act as data processors to your information.
When you subscribe to, purchase a membership from, or interact with a Creator on Locals Services, you give permission for that Creator to access certain personal information, which may include:
name and public Profile data, including profile photo
links to your social media
email address
phone number
information about your membership, including amount, start date, membership tier (if applicable).
date and time when the membership request or interaction was initiated
your communications with Creators through messages or questionnaires within Locals Services
We treat your privacy seriously, so Locals maintains a Data Processing Addendum for Creators that governs how creators can handle that shared information. This agreement requires Creators to safeguard their Members' privacy both during their time on Locals and beyond their Locals relationship. You can view the Creator Data Processing Addendum in this Privacy Policy below (Appendix B).
Creators also may work with third-party services to organize events or provide benefits to their community. In these cases, creators might share member data with these services, or members may choose to share their information directly to access specific offerings or participate in events. We recommend reviewing the privacy policies of any third-party services to understand their data practices.
Third-Party content and integrations
Our Locals Services may contain third-party content and integrations, such as ChatGPT that we use to suggest personalized ideas for activities. Through these integrations, you may be providing information to the third party as well as to Locals (or we may do so on your behalf). We are not responsible for how those third parties collect or use your information. As always, we encourage you to review the privacy policies of every third-party service that you visit or use, including those third parties you interact with through our services.
Suggested personalized ideas for activities
We have a feature to suggest personalized ideas for activities based on your goals, interests, bio, occupation, professional area, gender, age, location (city or place), gender (“
Input Data”)
. By using our Locals Services, you acknowledge the processing of your data using generative AI tools for the purpose of personalized ideas for activities.
How it works
This feature is based on ChatGPT. ChatGPT is a natural language processing tool that analyzes your Input Data to provide recommendations. When you create your account in Locals and provide your Input Data, we send a query to ChatGPT together with the Input Data and receive a reply that has been drafted by ChatGPT. Locals operates a ChatGPT account and interacts with the ChatGPT software on your behalf; so you do not need to have your own account with ChatGPT.
Your Input Data will be used solely for the purpose of suggesting personalized ideas for activities and will not be used to train ChatGPT. Suggested personalized ideas for activities that  you have “liked” on your Locals profile, will be available on your account and profile and may be visible to other users. You can edit, remove or delete these activities at any time.
To learn more about how ChatGPT processes your data, please see the ChatGPT Privacy Policy at [
https://openai.com/policies/privacy-policy
].
Disclaimer
Please note that the suggestions provided by ChatGPT are not guaranteed to be accurate or suitable for your specific circumstances. We do not assume responsibility for the results of using this feature. If you are not satisfied with the result of the suggested personalized idea for activity, you may simply “dislike” it, refrain from “liking” it. You can always contact our support team at
privacy@locals.org
, we will do our best to address your concerns and find a solution that meets your needs.
Opt-out
If you wish to opt-out of this feature you may remove suggestions in your profile.
Personalised cover for your activity generated by AI
If you grant us permission to access your camera, your device’s photo library or your contact list, we will process the photos you select to upload to Locals to provide features of the app that you choose to use.
The following describes how we process, share, and retain your photos, and Image Data in connection with the feature for the creation of  personalized cover for activity feature, generated by artificial intelligence of the Locals app (AI RSVP).
AI RSVP.
When you upload photos to Locals to use this feature, we process your photos using technology that identifies a face on the photo (collectively, “Image Data”).
When uploading photos that include individuals other than yourself, you are confirming that you have obtained all the necessary consents from these individuals to upload their photos to Locals.
If you have uploaded a photo to Locals to create AI RSVP, we will use artificial intelligence technology to generate new images using the Image Data. This processing only occurs on your device and is not stored on our servers. Image Data will be used solely for the purpose of creating new images in AI RSVP and will not be used to train any technology and/or create separate artificial intelligence outputs or products.
The new content created using AI RSVP will be available on your account and profile, if you choose to share it, and may be visible to other users. You can edit, remove or delete this content and/or the activities to which the content relates at any time.
Links to other sites
For the convenience of our visitors and clients, Locals Services may contain links to other sites, such as those of our partners or vendors, which are subject to different privacy policies. The Policy will not apply to your use of other websites. While we generally try to link only to sites that share similar high standards and respect for privacy, we have no responsibility or liability for the content, products or services offered, independent actions, or the privacy and security practices employed by these other independent sites. We encourage you to ask questions and review the applicable privacy policies found on such other websites, services and applications to understand how your information may be collected and used on these independent sites before disclosing information to third parties.
How long is your information kept
We will retain your Personal Data only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy.
Account deletion.
We delete most of your information after you delete your account, unless we are required to keep it for longer for limited legal purposes or for our legitimate interest purporses. It means that we will retain your Personal Data until you delete your account or request us to delete your data (by contacting us at
privacy@locals.org
). Once we have deleted your Personal Data, you will not be able to exercise the right to access, the right to erasure, the right to rectification or the right to data portability.
Please note that deletion of App does not imply the deletion of your account and your data
Photo verification data retention.
We retain the scans so that we can verify you in the future and to audit and manage our photo verification feature until we no longer need them for such purposes. After the applicable retention period expires, we take commercially reasonable steps to permanently and securely delete the scans from our systems. Photo verification data are only created and retained with your consent for the duration of the Photo Verification process. Photo Verification may take up to 24 hours. Once your Photo Verification is complete, the verification information is deleted. We retain screenshots from the photo selfie that you took for the purposes outlined above, but the Photo Verification information pulled from your photo is deleted.
You can request deletion of the scans by
privacy@locals.org
. In any event, this information is deleted upon account closure.
Retention to comply with legal obligations.
We may retain your Personal data in connection with your privacy-related requests and communications with us, if any, as necessary to comply with our legal obligations, to resolve disputes, and to enforce our agreements.
We delete your data and only keep limited information for specified purposes, as laid out below:
We must keep it to comply with applicable law (for instance, if you make purchases within the Locals Services, some personal data may be kept for tax and accounting purposes);
We must keep it to evidence our compliance with applicable law (for example, if an account is blocked, we keep some account information and a record of the behavior that led to the block - this information is retained for evidential purposes in case of queries or legal claims concerning the block);
There is an outstanding issue, claim or dispute requiring us to keep the relevant information until it is resolved; or
The information must be kept for our legitimate business interests, such as fraud prevention and enhancing Users’ safety and security (for example, information may need to be kept to prevent a user who was banned for unsafe behavior or security incidents from opening a new account).
Usage data.
We may retain usage data associated with the deleted account for the purposes of ensuring the security and integrity of our systems, supporting business analysis and improving our services. We will ensure that any usage data retained after account deletion is securely stored and used only for the aforementioned purposes.
Anonymized Data.
Even if we delete some or all of your Personal Data, we may continue to retain and use anonymized data previously collected that can no longer be used for personal identification.
How do we secure your information
We maintain appropriate organizational and technological safeguards to help protect against unauthorized use, access to or accidental loss, alteration or destruction of the personal information we hold. We also seek to ensure our third-party service providers do the same.
We will endeavor to use the least amount of personal information as is required for each purpose. We will employ pseudonymisation and anonymisation techniques, where appropriate.
Our staff will access your personal information on a “need to know” basis.
Unfortunately, the transmission of personal data through the internet is not completely secure. Although we will do our best to protect your personal data, we cannot guarantee the security of your personal data transmitted to or stored on our IT system, and any transmission is at your own risk. Once we have received your personal data, we will use strict procedures and security features to try to prevent unauthorized access.
Where is your information processed
We may transfer your personal information to our group companies, suppliers and other third parties in countries different to your country of residence.
In addition, data may be transferred to our subsidiaries or processors in third countries or subcontractors of our processors in third countries.
We and certain of our service providers are incorporated in the United States. Accordingly, your Personal Data may be transferred to and stored in the United States.
Where required under the EEA General Data Protection Regulation (
"GDPR"
), in case of transfers of personal data from the EEA to countries outside the EEA, where we cannot rely on adequacy decisions adopted by the European Commission (for more information, please see
here
) we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to guarantee the continued protection of your personal data, particularly by signing the Standard Contractual Clauses of the European Commission (article 46(2)(c) GDPR). For more information on these Standard Contractual Clauses, please see
here
.
Where required under the UK General Data Protection Regulation (
"UK GDPR"
), in case of transfers of personal data to countries outside the United Kingdom, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place to guarantee the continued protection of your personal data, particularly by signing the UK Addendum to the EU Standard Contractual Clauses or the UK International Data Transfer Agreement, whichever is more appropriate in the given situation. For more information on UK Addendum and the UK International Data Transfer Agreement please see
here
. We may also guarantee the protection of your personal data by relying on adequacy decisions adopted or approved by the authorities in the United Kingdom
Our policy regarding children
We appreciate the need to provide extra privacy protections to users who are children. Locals Services are intended for general audiences over the
age of 18 years
(or of age of legal majority where you live, if different). We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from or direct or target interest based advertising to anyone under the age of 18 or knowingly allow such persons to use Locals Services. If you are under 18, please do not send any information about yourself to us, including your name, address, telephone number, or email address. No one under the age of 18 may provide any personal information. In the event that we learn that we have collected personal information from a child under age 18, we will delete that information as quickly as possible. If you believe that we might have any information from or about a child under the age of 18, please contact us.
Electronic communications
By using Locals, you also agree to receive electronic communications from us, including via email, push notifications and by posting notices on Locals. The communications between you and us may take place via electronic means, whether you use Locals or send us emails, or whether we post notices on Locals or communicate with you via email. These communications may include notices about Locals and Subscriptions and are part of your relationship with us. For contractual purposes, you: (i) consent to receive communications from us in an electronic form; and (ii) agree that all terms and conditions, agreements, notices, disclosures, and other communications that we provide to you electronically satisfy any legal requirement that such communications would satisfy if it were to be in writing. The foregoing does not affect your statutory rights. Communications from us and our affiliated companies may include but are not limited to: operational communications concerning your Account or the use of Locals (e.g., technical and security notices, updates to this Privacy Policy and Locals Terms of Use), and updates concerning new and existing features (e.g., changes/updates to features of Locals and their scope, prices of in-app subscriptions).
You may opt-out of receiving promotional emails from us at any time through any of the following methods:
by following the opt-out links in any promotional email sent to you;
by contacting us at any time at
privacy@locals.org
;
You may opt-out of push notifications by changing the settings on your mobile device.
Contact us
