Appendix B. Creators Data Processing Addendum (DPA)
This Data Processing Agreement (
”DPA”
) governs the processing of personal data by Locals, acting as the Controller, and the Creator, acting as the Processor, in compliance with applicable Data Protection Law.
To facilitate the better direct connection with Members and Creators, Locals may share the Personal Data of Members with Creators. Creators then process Members’ Personal Data in order to provide Members with any and all offerings as part of the Creator’s activities on Locals Services. Locals requires all Creators to agree to this Data Processing Addendum to ensure that Creators respect the privacy rights of Members when processing their Personal Data.
This Privacy Promise is between Locals and Creators, taking effect from the moment a Locals profile is created (i.e. Creator is engaged) and applies exclusively to the Personal Data of Members collected by Creators and provided to Creators for the purpose of running a their communities within Locals Services.
This DPA is an extension of the Locals Privacy Policy and outlines certain requirements for Creators to process Personal Data during and beyond their relationship with Locals.
1. Definitions
For the purposes of this Agreement:
"Personal Data"
: Any information relating to an identified or identifiable individual, such as email addresses, that is provided to the Processor by the Controller.
"Processing"
: Any operation or set of operations performed on Personal Data, such as collection, storage, use, disclosure, or destruction.
"Data Subject"
: An individual whose Personal Data is processed under this Agreement.
"Subprocessor"
: A third-party service provider engaged by the Processor to assist in processing Personal Data.
"Data Protection Law"
: All applicable laws relating to privacy and the processing of personal data that may exist in any relevant jurisdiction, including supervisory authorities' guidance and codes of practice. This includes, but is not limited to, the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), European Directives 95/46/EC and 2002/58/EC (as amended), and any implementing legislation or regulations that amend, replace, or consolidate these laws.
2. Purpose of the DPA
This DPA outlines the relationship between
Locals
as the Controller and the
Creator
as the Processor, detailing the terms under which personal data is processed. It ensures compliance with relevant data protection laws and establishes responsibilities for both parties regarding the processing of personal data.
3. Scope
Scope.
The parties acknowledge that
Locals
is the
data controller
and the
Creator
is the
data processor
with respect to the personal data of users members of their communities, club or paid activity (referred to as "User Data") that the Creator processes in connection with providing users any and all products or services as part of that Creator's membership business on Locals ("Creators Services"). The subject matter of the data processing, the types of personal data, and the categories of data subjects will be limited to what is necessary for the performance of Creators Service. The processing activities covered by this agreement will be conducted by the Creator once they have left the Locals platform. The key elements of the data processing under this Privacy Notice are as follows:
Subject Matter of Data Processing:
User Data
Duration of Processing:
As long as the Creator retains User Data for Creator`s Service.
Nature and Purpose of Processing:
Limited to the Creator's provision of Creator`s Services to the user.
Types of Personal Data:
Contact details, including but not limited to, username, email address and transaction details.
Categories of Data Subjects:
Locals users who subscribe to membership of Creator on Locals.
Analytics Data.
Controller acknowledges and agrees that Processor may create and derive from Processing related to the Service anonymized and/or aggregated data that does not identify Customer or any Data Subject ("
Analytics Data
"), and use, publicize or share with third parties such Analytics Data to improve the Service and for Processor's other legitimate business purposes.
4. Roles and responsibilities
Locals as the Controller:
Locals determines the purposes and means of processing personal data collected from users of Creators.
Creators as the Processor:
Creators will process User Data only in accordance with the Locals Terms of Service, Privacy Policy and this DPA and only in compliance with Data Protection Law. The nature and purpose of the processing shall be limited to that necessary to carry out such instructions, and not for Creator's own purposes, or for any other purpose except as required by law. If Creator is required by law to process the personal data for any other purpose, Creator will inform Locals of such requirement prior to the processing unless prohibited by law from doing so.
5. Data collection and use
The personal data processed may include, but is not limited to, names, surnames, email phone number, transaction details, communication records, request timestamps, membership tier information, subscription pricing, and questionnaire responses (with visibility settings as configured by the creator). The Controller (Locals) authorizes the Processor (Creator) to process this data only in accordance with written instructions and applicable Data Protection Laws.
The Processor shall:
Process data only as reasonably necessary to provide the Services
Implement appropriate security measures and maintain records of all processing activities
Not process data in any way that could lead to a breach of Data Protection Laws
The Controller (Locals) maintains sole responsibility for determining the purposes and manner of data processing. After anonymization, data that is no longer personally identifiable may be used for other purposes.
Facilitating platform functionality
Ensuring secure transactions
Providing support and analytics tools
6. Data Security
Creator will implement and maintain appropriate technical and organizational measures designed to protect the personal data against unauthorized or unlawful processing and against accidental loss, destruction, damage, theft, alteration or disclosure. The measures shall be appropriate to the harm which might result from any unauthorized or unlawful processing, accidental loss, destruction, damage or theft of the personal data and having regard to the nature of the personal data which is to be protected and as a minimum shall be in accordance with the Data Protection Law.
7. Sub-processors
The Processor (Creator) may engage sub-processors to perform services, such as payment processing and cloud storage, but must inform the Controller (Locals) in advance of any such engagement. The Processor ensures that any sub-processors comply with the same data protection obligations.
Personnel.
The Processor (Creator) shall ensure the reliability and competence of any personnel who have access to User Data, and ensure they are informed of its confidential nature and comply with the obligations in this DPA.
8. Data retention
Personal data is retained only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this agreement or to comply with legal obligations. Upon termination of the Creator's account, the Processor (Creator) will delete or anonymize any personal data unless otherwise required by law.
9. Data subject rights
The Controller (Locals) will assist the Processor (Creator) in complying with data subjects' rights, including:
Right to access, rectification, and deletion of personal data.
Right to data portability and to object to data processing.
The Processor (Creator) is responsible for directly communicating with supporters regarding the exercise of these rights.
10. International data transfers
The Controller (Locals) ensures that all international transfers of personal data are carried out in compliance with applicable data transfer laws, utilizing safeguards such as Standard Contractual Clauses or equivalent mechanisms.
Transfer to Third Parties.
Creator will not give access to or transfer any personal data to any third party (including any affiliates, group companies or subcontractors) without the prior consent of Locals. Creator must ensure the reliability and competence of all third parties, employees, or agents who may have access to personal data processed in the provision of Creator's Services. Any contract with such third parties must include data protection provisions that are equivalent to those in this DPA and the Terms of Service, and must comply with applicable Data Protection Law.
11. Personal data breaches
If Creator becomes aware of any Personal Data Breach affecting any Customer Data, they must:
Notify Locals without undue delay after becoming aware of the breach
Provide Locals with all necessary information to enable notification to competent data protection authorities and/or affected Data Subjects, if required by Data Protection Laws
Assist Locals with information to meet obligations to inform Data Subjects or Data Protection authorities of the Personal Data Breach
Take immediate action to investigate and contain the breach
Implement necessary recovery actions at their own expense
Locals is responsible for complying with Personal Data Breach notification requirements and fulfilling any third-party notification obligations. Creator's notice of or response to a Personal Data Breach will not be considered an acknowledgment or admission of fault or liability.
12. Compliance with data protection regulations
Creator shall comply at all times with and assist Locals in complying with its applicable obligations under Data Protection Law. Creator shall provide reasonable information requested by Locals to demonstrate compliance with the obligations set out in this Privacy Promise. Creator will notify Locals immediately if, in Creator's opinion, an instruction for the processing of personal data given by Locals violates any country's data privacy legislation.
Creator will take all reasonable steps to assist Locals in complying with applicable Data Protection Law, including:
Promptly informing Locals of any data subject requests or complaints
Following Locals' standard terms of service regarding liability
Indemnifying Locals for data processing activities under Creator's instructions
13. Data retention and DPA duration
Creator will not retain personal data longer than necessary to provide Creator`s Services. Upon service completion or user request, Creator must securely destroy or return all personal data to Locals.
This DPA remains valid as long as the Creator continues to use Locals' services. Any amendments to this agreement will be communicated in advance and may require mutual consent.
